  "strategy": [
    "Always transition to goal_stop and stop when marker_close is detected.",
    "When marker_seen, switch to marker_track and approach the marker using move_to_marker.",
    "If marker_lost during tracking/approach, switch to scan_full to reacquire the marker.",
    "After obstacle detection, transition to the corresponding obstacle state and use a consistent escape (rotate_commit_cw for obs_left, rotate_commit_ccw for obs_right, scan_full for obs_front).",
    "After any recovery or committed action, pass through scan_full or clear before resuming forward progress.",
    "In clear, allow both move_forward and full_rotate to balance exploration and marker search.",
    "Avoid oscillations by using a fixed turn direction for each obstacle side.",
    "All uncontrollable events are handled in every state; non-critical ones self-loop in action/commit states.",
    "No infinite controllable loops; all commit/scan/recovery states are one-shot.",
    "No move_forward from obs_front; always require a recovery/scan step first."
  ]
